%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F5e28e74262fa810254452d84%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221331%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3ENASA%20astronauts%20Bob%20Behnken%20(left)%20and%20Doug%20Hurley%20(right)%20were%20the%20first%20people%20to%20fly%20aboard%20a%20private%20spaceship%2C%20SpaceX's%20Crew%20Dragon.%3Cp%3ESpaceX%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EWith%20each%20flight%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Felon-musk-spacex-valuation-175-billion-more-disney-comcast-2023-12%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3ESpaceX%20has%20earned%20money%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20while%20Boeing%20has%20been%20sinking%20more%20and%20more%20funds%20into%20Starliner.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMusk%2C%20who%20founded%20SpaceX%20in%202002%2C%20pointed%20out%20the%20disparity%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Felon-musk-problems-twitter-x-tesla-gamble-luck-run-out-2023-12%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eon%20X%3C%2Fa%3E%20on%20Monday%20morning.%20He%20attributed%20it%20to%20%26quot%3Btoo%20many%20non-technical%20managers%20at%20Boeing.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%20data-script%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fplatform.twitter.com%2Fwidgets.js%5C%22%20data-styles%3D%5C%22default-width%5C%22%20data-embed-type%3D%5C%22twitter%5C%22%20data-type%3D%5C%22embed%5C%22%3E%3Cblockquote%20class%3D%5C%22twitter-tweet%5C%22%3E%3Cp%20lang%3D%5C%22en%5C%22%20dir%3D%5C%22ltr%5C%22%3EAlthough%20Boeing%20got%20%244.2%20billion%20to%20develop%20an%20astronaut%20capsule%20and%20SpaceX%20only%20got%20%242.6%20billion%2C%20SpaceX%20finished%204%20years%20sooner.%20%3Cbr%3E%3Cbr%3ENote%2C%20the%20crew%20capsule%20design%20of%20Dragon%202%20has%20almost%20nothing%20in%20common%20with%20Dragon%201.%20%3Cbr%3E%3Cbr%3EToo%20many%20non-technical%20managers%20at%20Boeing.%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ft.co%2FbTXWAfxfrh%5C%22%3Ehttps%3A%2F%2Ft.co%2FbTXWAfxfrh%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%E2%80%94%20Elon%20Musk%20(%40elonmusk)%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ftwitter.com%2Felonmusk%2Fstatus%2F1787531120852312388%3Fref_src%3Dtwsrc%255Etfw%5C%22%3EMay%206%2C%202024%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fblockquote%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%3Cp%3EMusk%20was%20reposting%20an%20Ars%20Technica%20article%20by%20the%20publication's%20senior%20space%20editor%20Eric%20Berger%2C%20which%20laid%20out%20in%20detail%20how%20%26quot%3BBoeing%20decisively%20lost%20the%20commercial%20crew%20space%20race%2C%20and%20it%20proved%20to%20be%20a%20very%20costly%20affair.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%222200%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22spaceship%20grey%20and%20white%20shaped%20like%20a%20gumdrop%20with%20Boeing%20logo%20and%20American%20flag%20on%20it%20hanging%20above%20a%20metal%20platform%20with%20workers%20in%20hardhats%20surrounding%20a%20hole%20with%20cutaway%20rocket%20segment%20below%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F6635551dec0c696569010fd5%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221466%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EThe%20Boeing%20CST-100%20Starliner%20spacecraft%20is%20guided%20into%20position%20above%20an%20Atlas%20V%20rocket%20for%20an%20uncrewed%20test%20flight.%3Cp%3ENASA%2FCory%20Huston%20via%20Reuters%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EThere%20were%20clear%20technical%20reasons%20for%20the%20delays.%20During%20Starliner's%20first%20attempt%20to%20fly%20to%20the%20ISS%20without%20a%20crew%2C%20software%20errors%20forced%20it%20to%20return%20to%20Earth%20early.%20Then%20a%20series%20of%20issues%2C%20including%20dysfunctional%20valves%20in%20the%20propulsion%20system%2C%20caused%20further%20delays.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20commentators%20like%20Musk%20and%20Berger%20say%20there's%20an%20underlying%20cause.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20Commercial%20Crew%20Program%20represents%20a%20major%20shift%20in%20how%20NASA%20sees%20its%20contractors.%20Going%20forward%2C%20from%20space%20stations%20to%20the%20moon%20to%20Mars%2C%20NASA%20wants%20to%20foster%20a%20new%20competitive%20economy%20in%20space.%20Rather%20than%20the%20entity%20running%20everything%2C%20the%20agency%20wants%20to%20be%20one%20of%20many%20customers%20on%20companies'%20space%20stations%2C%20spaceships%2C%20and%20lunar%20bases.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThat's%20part%20of%20why%20Crew%20Dragon%20and%20Starliner%20were%20on%20fixed-price%20contracts.%20NASA%20set%20the%20price%2C%20and%20then%20SpaceX%20and%20Boeing%20had%20to%20build%20and%20fly%20the%20spaceships%20to%20NASA's%20specifications.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAfter%20all%2C%20the%20companies%20would%20have%20other%20customers%20on%20their%20spaceships.%20They%20weren't%20building%20them%20just%20for%20the%20government.%20So%20it's%20on%20them%20if%20costs%20start%20to%20balloon.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThat's%20an%20adjustment%20for%20Boeing%20as%20a%20legacy%20contractor%20for%20the%20Department%20of%20Defense%20and%20NASA%2C%20aerospace%20expert%20George%20Nield%20previously%20told%20Business%20Insider.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBoeing%20was%20used%20to%20the%20government%20paying%20all%20of%20its%20expenses%20to%20deliver%20the%20best%20possible%20product.%20Under%20that%20model%2C%20Berger%20explained%2C%20%26quot%3Bcost%20overruns%20and%20delays%20were%20not%20the%20company's%20problem%20%E2%80%94%20they%20were%20NASA's.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESuddenly%2C%20with%20a%20fixed%20price%2C%20%26quot%3Bit's%20up%20to%20the%20company%20to%20figure%20out%20what%20risks%20to%20take%20in%20terms%20of%20new%20technologies%20and%20new%20approaches%2C%26quot%3B%20said%20Nield%2C%20who%20is%20a%20former%20associate%20administrator%20of%20the%20FAA's%20Office%20of%20Commercial%20Space%20Transportation.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAdjusting%20to%20the%20fixed-price%20model%20was%20a%20challenge%20for%20Boeing%2C%20which%20has%20long%20had%20the%20luxury%20of%20moving%20slowly.%20Scrappy%20SpaceX%2C%20however%2C%20was%20%26quot%3Bin%20its%20natural%20environment%2C%26quot%3B%20as%20Berger%20put%20it.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EA%20spokesperson%20told%20Berger%20that%20%26quot%3Bchallenges%20arise%20when%20the%20fixed%20price%20acquisition%20approach%20is%20applied%20to%20serious%20technology%20development%20requirements%2C%20or%20when%20the%20requirements%20are%20not%20firmly%20and%20specifically%20defined%20resulting%20in%20trades%20that%20continue%20back%20and%20forth%20before%20a%20final%20design%20baseline%20is%20established.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAccording%20to%20Berger%2C%20the%20spokesperson%20added%3A%20%26quot%3BA%20fixed%20price%20contract%20offers%20little%20flexibility%20for%20solving%20hard%20problems%20that%20are%20common%20in%20new%20product%20and%20capability%20development.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Felon-musk-bashes-boeing-astronaut-flight-spacex-did-years-ago-2024-5%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1715039858000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F663952fc10dfcda409674800%3Fformat%3Djpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Felon-musk-bashes-boeing-astronaut-flight-spacex-did-years-ago-2024-5%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22SpaceX%20flew%20its%20first%20NASA%20astronauts%20to%20the%20space%20station%20four%20years%20sooner%20and%20%241.6%20billion%20cheaper%20than%20Boeing.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22mmcfalljohnsen%40businessinsider.com%20(Morgan%20McFall-Johnsen)%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A305%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Felon-musk-bashes-boeing-astronaut-flight-spacex-did-years-ago-2024-5%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Pakistan%20SC%20suspends%20Peshawar%20HC%20order%20denying%20reserved%20seats%20to%20Imran-backed%20party%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%22%2C%22published%22%3A1715039257000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fstatic.toiimg.com%2Fphoto%2Fmsid-109898982%2Cimgsize-1367700.cms%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Ftimesofindia.indiatimes.com%2Fworld%2Fpakistan%2Fpakistan-sc-suspends-peshawar-hc-order-denying-reserved-se