20holds%20a%20sample%20of%20tungsten%20in%20a%20glass%20jar%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F66394aac10dfcda409674605%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22651%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3ETungsten%20is%20a%20heavy%20metal%20that%20WEST%20uses%20in%20its%20tokamak%20because%20of%20its%20heat-resistant%20properties.%3Cp%3EJulian%20Stratenschulte%2Fpicture%20alliance%20via%20Getty%20Images%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EWEST%20is%20helping%20scientists%20test%20the%20best%20materials%20for%20building%20the%20walls%20inside%20a%20fusion%20reactor%2C%20which%20isn't%20easy%20since%20these%20environments%20can%20reach%20temperatures%20more%20than%20three%20times%20hotter%20than%20the%20sun's%20center.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOriginally%2C%20WEST%20contained%20carbon%20walls.%20While%20carbon%20is%20easy%20to%20work%20with%2C%20Delgado-Aparicio%20said%2C%20it%20also%20absorbs%20tritium%2C%20a%20rare%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Foppenheimer-science-to-understand-physics-atomic-bombs-2023-7%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ehydrogen%20isotope%3C%2Fa%3E%20that%20fuels%20the%20fusion%20reaction.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BImagine%20you%20have%20a%20wall%20that%20is%20not%20only%20a%20wall%2C%20but%20it's%20some%20sort%20of%20a%20sponge%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said%2C%20%26quot%3Ba%20sponge%20that%20absorbs%20your%20fuel.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESo%2C%20in%202012%2C%20scientists%20decided%20to%20test%20a%20different%20material%20for%20the%20tokamak's%20walls%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Ftungsten-cube-sold-on-amazon-sell-for-thousands-crypto-community-2021-11%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Etungsten%3C%2Fa%3E%20%E2%80%94%20the%20same%20material%20that%20ITER%20will%20use%20for%20some%20of%20its%20main%20components.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%222000%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Three%20men%20in%20white%20lab%20coats%20sit%20at%20a%20desk%20looking%20at%20a%20computer%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F66353ea2ec0c6965690103fb%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221281%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3ETullio%20Barbui%2C%20Novimir%20Pablant%2C%20and%20Luis%20Delgado-Aparicio%20examine%20the%20results%20of%20the%20WEST%20tokamak%20experiment.%3Cp%3EDECTRIS%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EBecause%20of%20tungsten's%20ability%20to%20withstand%20heat%20without%20absorbing%20tritium%2C%20Delgado-Aparicio%20believes%20it%20is%20the%20ideal%20material%20for%20tokamak%20walls.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThat%20said%2C%20tungsten%20isn't%20perfect.%20One%20of%20its%20downfalls%20is%20it%20can%20melt%20and%20enter%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Ffusion-startup-tokamak-energy-raises-87-million-2020-1%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ethe%20plasma%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20contaminating%20it.%20In%20turn%2C%20this%20can%20counteract%20the%20process%2C%20radiating%20a%20lot%20of%20energy%20away%20and%20cooling%20the%20plasma.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ETo%20optimize%20the%20system%2C%20scientists%20need%20to%20understand%20how%20exactly%20tungsten%20behaves%20and%20interacts%20with%20the%20plasma.%20That's%20what%20researchers%20are%20doing%20with%20WEST.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%22696%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22A%20purplish%20wavy%20line%20against%20a%20blue%20background%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F66354102ec0c696569010635%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22570%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EAn%20image%20of%20the%20plasma%20from%20the%20WEST%20tokamak.%3Cp%3EFrench%20Alternatives%20Energies%20and%20Atomic%20Energy%20Commission%20(CEA)%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20team%20at%20PPPL%20modified%20a%20diagnostic%20tool%3Cstrong%3E%20%3C%2Fstrong%3Ethat%20they%20used%20in%20this%20latest%20experiment%20from%20WEST.%20The%20tool%20helped%20the%20team%20accurately%20measure%20the%20plasma's%20temperature