0on%20the%20right%20are%20comparing%20his%20situation%20to%20that%20of%20Santos.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3ECuellar%20and%20his%20wife%20are%20accused%20of%20bribery%2C%20money%20laundering%2C%20and%20acting%20as%20an%20unregistered%20foreign%20agent%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EAccording%20to%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fs3.documentcloud.org%2Fdocuments%2F24648114%2Fcuellarindictment.pdf%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E54-page%20indictment%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20Cuellar%20and%20his%20wife%20accepted%20bribes%20from%20both%20Azerbaijan%20and%20a%20Mexican%20bank%20from%20December%202014%20to%20November%202021%2C%20doing%20so%20through%20a%20series%20of%20shell%20companies%20and%20intermediaries.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20indictment%20alleges%20that%20the%20couple%20collected%20roughly%20%24600%2C000%20in%20bribes%20%E2%80%94%20%24360%2C000%20from%20the%20State%20Oil%20Company%20of%20the%20Azerbaijan%20Republic%20and%20%24236%2C390%20from%20Banco%20Azteca.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20the%20case%20of%20Azerbaijan%2C%20Cuellar's%20been%20accused%20of%20using%20his%20position%20as%20a%20member%20of%20the%20House%20Appropriations%20Committee%20to%20influence%20legislation%20to%20the%20benefit%20of%20the%20oil-rich%20state.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWith%20Banco%20Azteca%2C%20Cuellar%20has%20been%20accused%20pressuring%20officials%20in%20the%20executive%20branch%20to%20pursue%20policies%20favorable%20to%20the%20bank%2C%20as%20will%20as%20introducing%20legislation%20to%20shield%20the%20payday%20lending%20industry%20from%20federal%20regulation.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20criminal%20counts%20against%20Cuellar%20and%20his%20wife%20include%3A%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cul%3E%3Cli%3E%3Cp%3E2%20counts%20of%20conspiracy%20to%20commit%20bribery%20of%20a%20federal%20official%20and%20to%20have%20a%20public%20official%20act%20as%20an%20agent%20of%20a%20foreign%20principal%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fli%3E%3C%2Ful%3E%3Cul%3E%3Cli%3E%3Cp%3E2%20counts%20of%20bribery%20of%20a%20federal%20official%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3E%3Cp%3E2%20counts%20of%20conspiracy%20to%20commit%20honest%20services%20wire%20fraud%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3E%3Cp%3E2%20counts%20of%20violating%20the%20ban%20on%20public%20officials%20acting%20as%20agents%20of%20a%20foreign%20principal%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3E%3Cp%3E1%20count%20of%20conspiracy%20to%20commit%20money%20laundering%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3E%3Cp%3E5%20counts%20of%20money%20laundering.%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fli%3E%3C%2Ful%3E%3Cp%3ECuellar%20has%20denied%20any%20wrongdoing%2C%20saying%20in%20a%20statement%20that%20he%20and%20his%20wife%20are%20%26quot%3Binnocent%20of%20these%20allegations%26quot%3B%20and%20that%20he%20still%20plans%20to%20seek%20reelection.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3EHe's%20the%20only%20anti-abortion%20House%20Democrat%20left%20%E2%80%94%20but%20party%20leadership%20helped%20save%20him%20two%20years%20ago%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EAside%20from%20his%20bribery%20scandal%2C%20Cuellar%20has%20been%20a%20top%20target%20of%20progressives%20for%20years%2C%20owing%20to%20his%20relatively%20conservative%20politics.%20He%20is%20the%20only%20House%20Democrat%20who%20voted%20against%20a%20bill%20to%20protect%20abortion%20rights%20nationwide%20during%20the%20last%20Congress%2C%20and%20he%20has%20previously%20received%20an%20%26quot%3BA%26quot%3B%20rating%20from%20the%20National%20Rifle%20Association.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ECuellar%20faced%20a%20stiff%20challenge%20in%202022%20from%20immigration%20lawyer%20Jessica%20Cisneros%2C%20who%20had%20the%20backing%20of%20progressives%20like%20Rep.%20Alexandria%20Ocasio-Cortez%20and%20Bernie%20Sanders.%20Ultimately%2C%20Cuellar%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fhenry-cuellar-jessica-cisneros-texas-28-runoff-live-results-2022-5%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ewon%20his%20primary%3C%2Fa%3E%20by%20less%20than%20300%20votes.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHe%20was%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fnancy-pelosi-backing-anti-abortion-henry-cuellar-supreme-court-2022-5%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E