rsonal-finance%2Finvesting-rating-methodology%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ehow%20we%20rate%20investing%20products%3C%2Fa%3E%20to%20write%20unbiased%20product%20reviews.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%221600%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22hanna%20horvath%20headshot%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F6262eca09f6566001906483d%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22800%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EThe%20author%2C%20financial%20planner%20Hanna%20Horvath.%3Cp%3ECourtesy%20Hanna%20Horvath%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cul%3E%5Cn%3Cli%3EA%20401(k)%20is%20an%20excellent%20retirement%20savings%20account%2C%20but%20it%20shouldn't%20be%20the%20only%20one%20you%20choose.%3C%2Fli%3E%5Cn%3Cli%3EContribute%20up%20to%20your%20employer's%20match%2C%20then%20put%20money%20in%20a%20Roth%20account%20and%20a%20taxable%20account.%3C%2Fli%3E%5Cn%3Cli%3ETax%20diversification%20in%20retirement%20will%20protect%20you%20from%20changes%20in%20tax%20law%20and%20keep%20money%20flowing.%3C%2Fli%3E%5Cn%3C%2Ful%3E%3Cp%3ERetirement%20is%20an%20important%20financial%20goal%2C%20and%20there%20are%20many%20different%20ways%20to%20get%20there.%20A%20common%20path%20is%20via%20a%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fpersonal-finance%2Fwhat-is-401k%5C%22%3E401(k)%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20a%20pre-tax%20retirement%20plan%20offered%20by%20many%20employers.%20As%20a%20financial%20planner%2C%20I'm%20a%20big%20fan%20of%20these%20plans%20%E2%80%94%20they%20encourage%20automatic%20contributions%20and%20sometimes%20come%20with%20employer%20matching.%20But%2C%20I%20also%20believe%20you%20shouldn't%20be%20putting%20your%20whole%20nest%20egg%20in%20one%20basket.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMaybe%20you've%20heard%20about%20the%20power%20of%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fpersonal-finance%2Fwhat-is-diversification%5C%22%3Ediversification%3C%2Fa%3E%20when%20it%20comes%20to%20choosing%20your%20investments%20%E2%80%94%20investing%20in%20too%20much%20of%20one%20thing%20can%20open%20you%20up%20to%20more%20risk%20and%20make%20you%20susceptible%20to%20market%20swings.%20But%20did%20you%20know%20you%20should%20also%20diversify%20%3Cem%3Ewhere%20%3C%2Fem%3Eyou%20invest%3F%20When%20it%20comes%20to%20saving%20for%20retirement%2C%20I%20believe%20tax%20diversification%20is%20just%20as%20important%20as%20portfolio%20diversification.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ETaxes%20affect%20how%20much%20money%20you%20get%20to%20keep%20in%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fpersonal-finance%2Fbest-retirement-plans%5C%22%3Eretirement%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20and%20tax%20diversification%20is%20a%20strategy%20to%20help%20your%20money%20last.%20Your%20retirement%20accounts%20contain%20either%20tax-deferred%2C%20taxable%2C%20or%20tax-free%20funds.%20Creating%20a%20strategy%20that%20accounts%20for%20the%20various%20tax%20treatments%20of%20your%20accounts%20can%20help%20you%20save%20money%20and%20give%20you%20more%20flexibility%20in%20how%20you%20access%20your%20savings.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3EChoose%20both%20pre-%20and%20post-tax%20retirement%20accounts%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3ERetirement%20plans%20are%20made%20of%20either%20pre-tax%20or%20post-tax%20contributions%20(or%20a%20mix%20of%20both).%20Pre-tax%20contributions%2C%20typically%20found%20in%20your%20standard%20401(k)%2C%20reduce%20your%20income%20taxes%20during%20your%20pre-retirement%20years%2C%20while%20after-tax%20contributions%2C%20typically%20found%20in%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fpersonal-finance%2Fwhat-is-roth-ira%5C%22%3ERoth%20IRA%3C%2Fa%3E%20and%20Roth%20401(k)%20accounts%2C%20help%20reduce%20your%20tax%20burden%20in%20retirement.%20You%20can%20also%20save%20for%20retirement%20in%20traditional%20investing%20accounts%2C%20which%20are%20often%20after-tax%20contributions.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EPre-tax%20contributions%20allow%20you%20to%20delay%20paying%20taxes%20on%20contributions%20and%20earnings.%20For%20example%2C%20if%20you%20contribute%20to%20your%20company's%20401(k)%2C%20any%20money%20you%20add%20to%20it%20and%20any%20growth%20in%20your%20investments%20won't%20be%20taxed%20as%20long%20as%20the%20money%20stays%20in%20your%20account.%20When%20you%20retire%2C%20you'll%20pay%20taxes%2C%20but%20there's%20a%20chance%20you'll%20be%20taxed%20at%20a%20lower%20rate%20because%20your%20taxable%20income%20and%20tax%20bracket%20are%20lower%20than%20in%20your%20working%20years.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EPost-tax%20contributions%20provide%20tax-free%20income%20in%20your%20golden%20years%20and%20can%20reduce%20your%20overall%20tax%20burden%20in%20retirement.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3EThe%20benefits%20of%20tax%20diversification%20in%20retirement%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EInvesting%20in%20both%20pre-%20and%20post-tax%20retirement%20accounts%20gives%20you%20the%20best%20of%20both%20worlds.%20Having%20a%20balance%20between%20these%20two%20different%20tax%20streams%20offers%20more%20flexibility%20and%20sustainability%20for%20your%20savings%20and%20makes%20your%20accounts%20more%20resilient%20against%20future%20tax%20law%20changes.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHaving%20tax%20diversification%20helps%20provide%20some%20order%20in%20how%20you%20should%20take%20withdrawals%20in%20retirement%2C%20helping%20you%20structure%20your%20withdrawals%20to%20maximize%20your%20after-tax%20income.%20Typically%2C%20once%20you%20reach%20retirement%20age%2C%20you'll%20begin%20taking%20required%20minimum%20distributions%20from%20your%20accounts.%20To%20get%20the%20biggest%20benefit%2C%20you'll%20take%20distributions%20from%20tax-deferred%20accounts%2C%20and%20then%20distributions%20from%20tax-free%20accounts.%20Of%20course%2C%20it's%20important%20to%20consult%20your%20personal%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fpersonal-finance%2Fbest-online-financial-advisors%5C%22%3Efinancial%20advisor%3C%2Fa%3E%20or%20tax%20professional%20to%20get%20a%20specific%20tax-minimizing%20plan.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3EThe%203%20accounts%20you%20should%20consider%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3ESo%2C%20where%20should%20you%20be%20investing%3F%20I%20recommend%20a%20combination%20of%20a%20few%20different%20accounts.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMy%20rule%20of%20thumb%20is%20to%20invest%20first%20in%20your%20401(k)%2C%20if%20your%20company%20offers%20one.%20Make%20sure%20you're%20at%20least%20contributing%20up%20to%20your%20employer's%20annual%20maximum%20match%2C%20otherwise%20you're%20just%20leaving%20money%20on%20the%20table.%20If%20you%20have%20extra%20funds%20available%2C%20consider%20investing%20next%20in%20an%20after-tax%20account%20like%20a%20Roth%20IRA%20or%20Roth%20401(k).%20Keep%20in%20mind%20there%20is%20an%20income%20eligibility%20requirement%20for%20Roth%20IRAs.%20Lastly%2C%20consider%20a%20taxable%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fpersonal-finance%2Fbest-online-brokerage%5C%22%3Ebrokerage%20account%3C%2Fa%3E%20for%20the%20rest%20of%20your%20nest%20egg%20savings.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhat%20makes%20this%20strategy%20a%20winner%3F%20All%20withdrawals%20from%20your%20pre-tax%20retirement%20accounts%20are%20taxed%20as%20ordinary%20income%2C%20while%20all%20withdrawals%20from%20your%20taxable%20accounts%20(from%20the%20sale%20of%20stocks%20or%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fpersonal-finance%2Fmutual-funds%5C%22%3Emutual%20funds%3C%2Fa%3E)%20may%20be%20taxed%20at%20capital%20gains%20rates%2C%20depending%20on%20your%20income%20and%20how%20long%20you%20held%20the%20investment.%20Any%20withdrawals%20from%20your%20post-tax%20retirement%20accounts%20are%20completely%20tax-free.%20In%20other%20words%20%E2%80%94%20like%20the%20benefits%20of%20portfolio%20diversification%2C%20tax%20diversification%20reduces%20your%20overall%20risk%20from%20tax%20law%20changes%20or%20other%20policy%20changes.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOverall%2C%20the%20goal%20of%20retirement%20is%20to%20enjoy%20yourself%20after%20years%20of%20work.%20The%20last%20thing%20you%20want%20is