3A%2F%2Fwww.business-standard.com%2Ffinance%2Fnews%2Fgovt-adopted-pro-poor-approach-in-gst-implementation-fm-sitharaman-124050601088_1.html%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww-business--standard-com.cdn.ampproject.org%2Fc%2Fs%2Fwww.business-standard.com%2Famp%2Ffinance%2Fnews%2Fgovt-adopted-pro-poor-approach-in-gst-implementation-fm-sitharaman-124050601088_1.html%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.business-standard.com%2Famp%2Ffinance%2Fnews%2Fgovt-adopted-pro-poor-approach-in-gst-implementation-fm-sitharaman-124050601088_1.html%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Pregnant%20Minor's%20Views%20%26quot%3BImportant%20Factor%26quot%3B%20In%20Abortion%20Cases%3A%20Supreme%20Court%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cp%3EIn%20a%20significant%20order%2C%20the%20Supreme%20Court%20highlighting%20%26quot%3Bfundamental%20right%20under%20Article%2021%20of%20the%20Constitution%26quot%3B%20said%20that%20the%20opinion%20of%20a%20pregnant%20minor%20is%20an%20%26quot%3Bimportant%20factor%26quot%3B%20while%20deciding%20on%20abortion.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThe%20right%20to%20choose%20and%20reproductive%20freedom%20is%20a%20fundamental%20right%20under%20Article%2021%20of%20the%20Constitution.%20Therefore%2C%20where%20the%20opinion%20of%20a%20minor%20pregnant%20person%20differs%20from%20the%20guardian%2C%20the%20court%20must%20regard%20the%20view%20of%20the%20pregnant%20person%20as%20an%20important%20factor%20while%20deciding%20the%20termination%20of%20the%20pregnancy%2C%26quot%3B%20it%20said%20asserting%20that%20the%20consent%20of%20the%20pregnant%20person%20in%20matters%20of%20reproductive%20choices%20and%20abortion%20is%20%26quot%3Bparamount%26quot%3B.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20top%20court%20also%20advised%20medical%20boards%20evaluating%20a%20pregnant%20person%20with%20a%20gestational%20age%20above%20twenty-four%20weeks%20to%20%26quot%3Bopine%20on%20the%20physical%20and%20mental%20health%20of%20the%20person%26quot%3B.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EOn%20April%2029%2C%20the%20Supreme%20Court%20recalled%20its%20April%2022%20order%20by%20which%20it%20had%20permitted%20a%2014-year-old%20girl%20to%20undergo%20medical%20termination%20of%20her%2030-week%20pregnancy%20after%20her%20parents%20said%20they%20had%20decided%20to%20wait%20for%20the%20full%20term%20of%20pregnancy.%20The%20court%20was%20hearing%20a%20petition%20filed%20by%20the%20girl's%20mother%20challenging%20the%20Bombay%20High%20Court%20order%20declining%20the%20prayer%20for%20termination%20of%20pregnancy.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20Supreme%20Court%20had%20earlier%20allowed%20the%20rape%20survivor%20to%20terminate%20her%2030-week%20pregnancy%2C%20overturning%20an%20order%20by%20the%20High%20Court%2C%20calling%20it%20an%20%26quot%3Bexceptional%20case%26quot%3B%20and%20said%20the%20abortion%20was%20allowed%20based%20on%20a%20hospital%20report.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20its%20April%2029%20order%2C%20the%20court%20said%20the%20%26quot%3Bdelays%20caused%20by%20a%20change%20in%20the%20opinion%20of%20the%20medical%20board%26quot%3B%20or%20the%20procedures%20of%20the%20court%20%26quot%3Bmust%20not%20frustrate%26quot%3B%20the%20fundamental%20rights%20of%20pregnant%20people.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EUnder%20the%20Medical%20Termination%20of%20Pregnancy%20(MTP)%20Act%2C%20the%20upper%20limit%20for%20aborting%20the%20foetus%20is%2024%20weeks%20for%20married%20women%20as%20well%20as%20those%20in%20special%20categories%2C%20including%20rape%20survivors%20and%20other%20vulnerable%20women%2C%20such%20as%20those%20differently-abled%20and%20minors.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThe%20MTP%20Act%20does%20not%20allow%20any%20interference%20with%20the%20personal%20choice%20of%20a%20pregnant%20person%20in%20terms%20of%20proceeding%20with%20the%20termination.%20The%20Act%20leave%20no%20scope%20for%20interference%20by%20the%20family%20or%20the%20partner%20of%20a%20pregnant%20person%20in%20matters%20of%20reproductive%20choice%2C%26quot%3B%20stressed%20the%20top%20court.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20Supreme%20Court%20said%20that%20it%20recalled%20its%20earlier%20order%20allowing%20'X'%20to%20terminate%20her%20pregnancy%20as%20the%20decision%20was%20%26quot%3Bmade%20in%20light%20of%20the%20decisional%20and%20bodily%20autonomy%20of%20the%20pregnant%20person%20and%20her%20parents%26quot%3B.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIn%20the%20present%20case%2C%20the%20guardians%20of%20'X'%2C%20namely%20her%20parents%2C%20have%20also%20consented%20to%20taking%20the%20pregnancy%20to%20term.%20This%20is%20permissible%20as%20'X'%20is%20a%20minor%20and%20the%20consent%20of%20the%20guardian%20is%20prescribed%20under%20Section%203(4)(a)%20of%20the%20MTP%20Act%2C%26quot%3B%20it%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20court%20said%20the%20choice%20to%20continue%20the%20pregnancy%20to%20term%2C%20regardless%20of%20the%20court%20having%20allowed%20termination%20of%20the%20pregnancy%2C%20belongs%20to%20the%20individual%20alone.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EA%20bench%20of%20Chief%20Justice%20of%20India%20DY%20Chandrachud%2C%20Justices%20JB%20Pardiwala%20and%20Manoj%20Misra%20also%20clarified%20on%20why%20it%20used%20the%20term%20'pregnant%20person'%20instead%20of%20'pregnant%20woman'%20amid%20a%20debate%20over%20the%20use%20of%20gender-neutral%20vocabulary%20to%20identify%20the%20sexes.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWe%20use%20the%20term%20'pregnant%20person'%20and%20recognize%20that%20in%20addition%20to%20cisgender%20women%2C%20pregnancy%20can%20also%20be%20experienced%20by%20some%20non-binary%20people%20and%20transgender%20men%20among%20other%20gender%20identities%2C%26quot%3B%20the%20court%20stated%20in%20a%20footnote.%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1715007660000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fc.ndtvimg.com%2F2023-07%2F4qgfvaco_supreme-court-new_625x300_11_July_23.jpg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Findia-news%2Fpregnant-minors-views-important-factor-in-abortion-cases-supreme-court-5602795%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22In%20a%20significant%20order%2C%20the%20Supreme%20Court%20highlighting%20%26quot%3Bfundamental